  "text": "Photo by Julia Gartland When temps are pushing 90 and the air feels thick enough to drink, the only acceptable beverage is one that’s borderline slushy. I’m talking blender cocktails, boozy lemonades, fruit-forward frosés—the kind of drink you almost need a spoon for. Whether you’re craving something tart and citrusy or leaning tropical with coconut and rum, these frozen drink recipes are the move. They’re chill, refreshing, and just a little bit dramatic—in the best way possible. 1. Sunrise Slushie This mango slushie is giving tropical sunrise vibes with citrus, pineapple juice, and hibiscus tea. 2. Frozen Gin \u0026 Tonic Your favorite highball, just a whole lot icier (and honestly, more fun). 3. Frozen Malted Latte Coffee meets milkshake in this frozen latte with malt powder for a nostalgic twist. 4. Frozen Daiquiri The classic frozen rum drink—limey, simple, and endlessly sippable. 5. Frozen Peach Lemonade With Gin Gin and juicy peaches are a dream team in this frozen lemonade. 6. Frozen Vodka Lemonade with Berries A summery blend of vodka, lemon juice, and fresh berries, all blitzed into slushy perfection. 7. Frozen Piña Colada If you like Piña Coladas, this coconutty classic belongs in your blender. 8. Raspberry, Orange \u0026 Sparkling Rosé Slushies Fruity and bubbly with a touch of tang—this one’s for your next brunch party. 9. Frosé The internet-famous frozen rosé that never goes out of style 10. Frozen Watermelon Five-Spice Daiquiri Fresh watermelon meets warming five-spice in this flavorful, icy twist on a daiquiri. 11. Pineapple, Coconut \u0026 Tequila Slushy A riff on the piña colada with a splash of tequila instead of rum. 12. Red, White, and Blue Paloma Slushies Perfect for any hot day, not just the fourth—grapefruit-forward and totally festive. 13. Manhattan Slushies Yes, you can freeze a whiskey cocktail—and this boozy, bittersweet slush proves it. 14. Frozen Hot Buttered Rum A cool take on a cozy classic—like dessert in cocktail form. 15. Frozen Paper Plane A bold and bitter frozen cocktail that packs a punch (and looks good doing it). 16. Frozen Vodka Gimlet This frosty lime-forward drink is clean, crisp, and dangerously drinkable. What's your favorite frozen drink? Tell us about it in the comments! Currently covering trending food and home decor at Food52 (and never missing a chance to mention that I’ve read Ina Garten’s memoir). Popular on Food52",
