_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\" type=\"image/webp\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/cDrhP0L0mJabBP-gEHTybmiCb9I=/375x250/filters:format(webp)/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg, https://images.food52.com/JPPau9lIKCgP9NgVCg4U-cPIrr8=/750x500/filters:format(webp)/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/R71-NJsimj5fjZqeITMVVzcjMR8=/375x250/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg, https://images.food52.com/RkxC8d_sy5FvycJKe0iv5FIGVH4=/750x500/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg 2x\" alt=\"glasses of frozen peach gin lemonade \" width=\"1006\" height=\"670\" data-pin-media=\"https://images.food52.com/tOuaDnSm_K8aY-j7c-YZxJ3L2g4=/2000x2000/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg\" data-pin-url=\"https://food52.com/blog/28864-best-frozen-drink-recipes\" data-pin-description=\"16 Frozen Drink Recipes to Cool You Down Fast on Food52\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/R71-NJsimj5fjZqeITMVVzcjMR8=/375x250/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg, https://images.food52.com/RkxC8d_sy5FvycJKe0iv5FIGVH4=/750x500/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg 2x\" src=\"https://images.food52.com/tOuaDnSm_K8aY-j7c-YZxJ3L2g4=/2000x2000/1a6f2751-50b9-40e6-9247-bb588e6b08ed--2021-0610_sponsored_nolets_frozen-gin-peach_recipe_not-branded_3x2_julia-gartland_169_1-copy.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Julia Gartland \u003c/span\u003e\n            \u003c/p\u003e\n            \n\n        \n\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \u003cdiv\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eWhen temps are pushing 90 and the air feels thick enough to drink, the only acceptable beverage is one that’s borderline slushy. I’m talking blender cocktails, boozy lemonades, fruit-forward frosés—the kind of drink you almost need a spoon for. Whether you’re craving something tart and citrusy or leaning tropical with coconut and rum, these frozen drink recipes are the move. They’re chill, refreshing, and just a little bit dramatic—in the best way possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n              \u003ch3\u003e1. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/90258-sunrise-slushie\"\u003eSunrise Slushie\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eThis mango slushie is giving tropical sunrise vibes with citrus, pineapple juice, and hibiscus tea.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e2. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/85911-frozen-gin-and-tonic\"\u003eFrozen Gin \u0026amp; Tonic\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eYour favorite highball, just a whole lot icier (and honestly, more fun).\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e3. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/90252-frozen-malted-latte\"\u003eFrozen Malted Latte\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eCoffee meets milkshake in this frozen latte with malt powder for a nostalgic twist.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e4. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/37157-frozen-daiquiri\"\u003eFrozen Daiquiri\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eThe classic frozen rum drink—limey, simple, and endlessly sippable.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e5. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/85912-frozen-peach-lemonade-gin\"\u003eFrozen Peach Lemonade With Gin\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eGin and juicy peaches are a dream team in this frozen lemonade.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e6. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/76904-frozen-vodka-lemonade-with-berries\"\u003eFrozen Vodka Lemonade with Berries\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eA summery blend of vodka, lemon juice, and fresh berries, all blitzed into slushy perfection.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e7. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/36110-frozen-pina-colada\"\u003eFrozen Piña Colada\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eIf you like Piña Coladas, this coconutty classic belongs in your blender.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e8. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/80498-raspberry-orange-sparkling-rose-slushies\"\u003eRaspberry, Orange \u0026amp; Sparkling Rosé Slushies\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eFruity and bubbly with a touch of tang—this one’s for your next brunch party.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e9. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/76637-frose?srsltid=AfmBOoo1wSexCjNL8D2r_oT3aKYj3GW7SQZuQm3lUz9bn-2acbrOD0O6\"\u003eFrosé\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eThe internet-famous frozen rosé that never goes out of style\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e10. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/37132-frozen-watermelon-five-spice-daiquiri\"\u003eFrozen Watermelon Five-Spice Daiquiri\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eFresh watermelon meets warming five-spice in this flavorful, icy twist on a daiquiri.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e11. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/83122-tequila-pina-colada\"\u003ePineapple, Coconut \u0026amp; Tequila Slushy\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eA riff on the piña colada with a splash of tequila instead of rum.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e12. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/71711-red-white-and-blue-paloma-slushies\"\u003eRed, White, and Blue Paloma Slushies\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003ePerfect for any hot day, not just the fourth—grapefruit-forward and totally festive.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e13. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/62802-manhattan-slushies\"\u003eManhattan Slushies\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eYes, you can freeze a whiskey cocktail—and this boozy, bittersweet slush proves it.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e14. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/88497-frozen-hot-buttered-rum\"\u003eFrozen Hot Buttered Rum\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eA cool take on a cozy classic—like dessert in cocktail form.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e15. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/93173-frozen-paper-plane-cocktail\"\u003eFrozen Paper Plane\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eA bold and bitter frozen cocktail that packs a punch (and looks good doing it).\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003ch3\u003e16. \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/89337-frozen-vodka-gimlet\"\u003eFrozen Vodka Gimlet\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eThis frosty lime-forward drink is clean, crisp, and dangerously drinkable.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \u003chr/\u003e\n\n              \n              \u003ccenter\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eWhat\u0026#39;s your favorite frozen drink? Tell us about it in the comments!\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/center\u003e\n          \u003c/div\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n            \n            \n\n\n\n            \n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n\n    \u003cp\u003e\n      Currently covering trending food and home decor at Food52 (and never missing a chance to mention that I’ve read Ina Garten’s memoir).\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ch3\u003ePopular on Food52\u003c/h3\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
